{
  "texts": [
    "However, most respondents (> 80%) did not believe that AI would replace medical researchers, suggesting a balanced view that AI will serve as a complementary tool rather than a replacement for human expertise.",
    "The sentiment that AI will augment rather than replace human expertise aligns with the broader perspective in the AI community, often termed \"augmented intelligence\" [16].",
    "This perspective emphasizes the synergy between human intuition and AI's computational capabilities.",
    "While AI can handle vast amounts of data and rapidly perform complex calculations, human researchers bring domain expertise, critical thinking, and ethical considerations [17].",
    "This combination can lead to more robust and comprehensive research outcomes [16, 18]."
  ]
}